@Database Changes_To_V1.06.guide

@Node Main "Changes to HydraBBS between V1.05 and V1.06"

  Changes to HydraBBS between V1.05 and V1.06
  ===========================================

  Please read *ALL* of this file, or you won't know about some of the great
  new features of this release.

  Go on, it'll only take you a couple of minutes.

  This document is stored as HBBS:Docs/Misc/Upgrades/Changes_To_V1.06.Guide

  Details
  =======

  Sysop Information     - @{"More..." link SysopInformation}

  Developer Information - N/A

  Files Changed         - @{"More..." link FilesChanged}

@EndNode

@Node SysopInformation "Sysop Information"

  Sysop Information
  =================

  * FileID

    *IMPORTANT*

    DO NOT USE TXTExtract!

    Please use this included tool instead:

    HBBS:System/Amiga/CLI/Textract

    And change your HBBS:System/FileID config accordingly, please see
    HBBS:Storage/Example_Configs/System/FileID

    TXTExtract incorrectly truncates files (i.e. you lose information!)

  * @{"DupeCheck" link HBBS:Docs/Doors/DupeCheck.Guide/MAIN}

    Implemented "CHECKALLCONFS" @{"system option" link HBBS:Docs/Doors/DupeCheck.Guide/SystemOptions}, so that the dupe checker
    can optionally check all other conference upload paths.

  * ModifyDIZ, FileHistory

    Updated ANSI.

  * AccountEdit

    Fixed browsing/searching/editing of users past the 128th user in
    the user data file.  I passed a BYTE instead of a ULONG to HBBS_LoadUser().

  * XPR

    When a file is resumed, a message is written to the callerslog.

  * XPR,Hydra

    Updated the canceling part of these two doors.

    Oops, I broke the file-resuming when I implemented HBBS_OkToUpload()
    (which checks if another use has just is is still uploading a file of
    the same name) --> FIXED!

  * Control

    Fixed a memory leak.

    Set internal stack size to 4096 bytes

    Used the compiler options smallcode and smalldata to reduce executable
    size.

    Added lots of debugging routines to the source code (no effect on the
    executable that is released to you!

    If there is no screen-mode preferences file, (hbbs:system/data/ctrlscrprefs.cfg)
    Control now prompts for a screenode to use, I don't know why I didn't to this
    for V1.0... :-)  You can still use the Select_Mode utility if you want..

    Optimized the creation of ENV:HBBSScreenName

    Removed some unneeded init code.

    Great, just great,  I've had reports of people not being able to
    use particular screenmode, so I've been checking it out, only
    to find problems with the backfill stuff (again!, I thought it was
    sorted).  HBBS Works 100% without the backfill, so I've added
    an option to HBBS:System/data/CtrlScrnPrefs.CFG, UseBackfill=YES|NO
    which you should use if you get problems.  Please report back to
    me with details if you get this problem.

    Please see @{"HBBS:Docs/Configuration/CtrlScrPrefs.Guide" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/CtrlScrPrefs.Guide/MAIN}

    In trying to fix this problem I have done quite a bit of optimisation
    and found a few potential bugs, which have been fixed.

    What a total pain in the ass that was to fix, anyway, I found the cause
    of the screenmode problems!

    I was RecFill()'ing one column and one row too many, causing memory after
    each plane in the screen's bitmap to be overwritten.  This had the rather
    nasty effect of currupting memory of some very important structures on
    my machine!  It was difficult to trace because the area of memory
    overwritten was different each time, argh..

    Still, armed with CyberGuard, Mungwall and Sushi I managed to pin it
    down,  Am I good or what ? :-)

    The RectFill() that was causing the problem is the one that I had to use
    directly after opening a screen, because for some reason, when you use
    an SA_Backfill tag with OpenScreen() it DOES NOT call the backfill
    function.  And it *should*.  So I have to manually rectfill() the screen
    with the right background colour myself, and I passed it
    0,0,Scr->Height,Scr->Width instead of 0,0,Scr->Height-1,Scr->Width-1
    i.e. for a 640 width screen, pixels 0-640 were recfilled, instead of
    0-639 (640!) pixels.

    This seemed more critical when using Picasso 96 in high resolutions
    and when using PAL: High Res.  I am using a Cybergraphics 64/3D in my
    A4000T/060/PPC and a CyberGraphics64 in my A3000/040 myself and this
    problem never showed up at all.  *weird!*

    Blimey...

    I tell you, I nearly gave up on this one, it was doing my head in..

    Now I can get back to making HBBS better...  rather than fixing bugs..

  * XPR, Hydra, SysopListViewer, Node, UserViewer

    Updated to use BBSGlobal->ScreenInfo->UsingBackfill

  * HBBSCommon.library

    Changed the returned values for HBBS_OkToUpload()

  * Updated docs

    I've updated the docs a bit, check out @{"HBBS:Docs/Misc/Upgrades/UpgradeIndex.guide" link HBBS:Docs/Misc/Upgrades/UpgradeIndex.guide/MAIN}

@EndNode

